'''Jan Einar Greve''' (born 11 May 1933) is a Norwegian lawyer.

He graduated from the [[University of Oslo]] as [[cand.jur.]] in 1959, and worked as a solicitor from 1961. From 1963 he is a barrister, with the mandate to work with cases in the [[Supreme Court of Norway]].<ref name=hvem>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Bruzelius, Karin M. |encyclopedia=Hvem er hvem? |last= |first= |authorlink= |year=2008 |editor=[[Knut Olav Åmås]] |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo |isbn=978-82-03-23561-0 |pages=182 }}</ref>

Greve has been the chairman of the board of [[Bergen Bank]] (1970-1986, including its predecessor Bergens Privatbank), [[Rieber & Søn]] (1987-2000), Vesta Forsikring (1988-2003), Høyteknologisenteret (1989-present) and ''[[Bergens Tidende]]''.<ref name=hvem/> In 2007 he was proclaimed Knight, First Class of the [[Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bt.no/lokalt/bergen/tettpa/article337152.ece |archive-url=https://archive.is/20070808020716/http://www.bt.no/lokalt/bergen/tettpa/article337152.ece |dead-url=yes |archive-date=8 August 2007 |title=Jan Einar Greve ridder |date=3 February 2007 |work=Bergens Tidende |language=Norwegian |accessdate=8 December 2008 }}</ref>

