'''Kelvin Tak-On Chan''' (陳德安) is a Hong Kong youth entrepreneur (born on 23 October 1982).<ref>{{cite news|title=Double success at the Hong Kong Education UK Alumni Awards|url=http://www.mbs.ac.uk/news/school-news/double-success-at-the-hong-kong-education-uk-alumni-awards/|accessdate=14 February 2016|publisher=Alliance Manchester Business School}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kelvin Chan Tak On (Winner)|url=https://www.britishcouncil.hk/en/education-uk-alumni-awards-2016|publisher=British Council|accessdate=5 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=三港人獲英國傑出校友獎|url=https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E4%B8%89%E6%B8%AF%E4%BA%BA%E7%8D%B2%E8%8B%B1%E5%9C%8B%E5%82%91%E5%87%BA%E6%A0%A1%E5%8F%8B%E7%8D%8E-215724210.html|accessdate=5 February 2016|agency=Yahoo! NEWS|work=Sing Tao Daily |language=zh|date=27 January 2016}}</ref> Kelvin is the founder of Korean Corner, a Hong Kong-based importer selling Korean designed/ made products in February 2015.

== Early life ==
Kelvin was in Hong Kong in 1982.

== Tertiary education ==
After leaving secondary school in 1999, Kelvin has enrolled a higher diploma in computer science and a certificate in business management at The Education University of Hong Kong (it was The Hong Kong Institute of Education), and afterwards, [[The Open University of Hong Kong]].{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}

Besides, Kelvin has also completed his Bachelor of Arts (Hons) in Business Administration at [[University of Greenwich]] in 2011 and took up a Master's course in Business Administration at [[Manchester Business School]] of [[University of Manchester]] afterwards to extend his interest in business management.{{citation needed|date=August 2016}}

== Career ==
A conceptual store was firstly opened in [[Taipei]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Security Check Required|publisher = facebook.com|access-date = 5 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Korean Corner－有. 設計uDesign|url = http://www.koreancorner.com.tw|publisher = koreancorner.com.tw|access-date = 5 February 2016}}</ref> Followed by Korean Corner flagship showroom in Hong Kong to demonstrate their "powerful" and [[Environmentally friendly|eco-friendly]] paper products (e.g. close to 4m height paper dinosaur slide sitting in the middle of the showroom for every adult and kid to experience). In 2 years the company has expanded to [[Korea]], Australia and US. Japan and Singapore offices have been set up in Q3 of 2018, and now planning on the next step in Vietnam, Estonia and Canada.

Kelvin has been interviewed by media on his new business model that he has lots of new ideas and combined with the concepts he learned in school to develop it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bizhkmag.com/#!%25E5%25B1%258B%25E6%259D%2591%25E5%25B0%258F%25E5%25AD%2590%25E3%2580%258C%25E7%25B4%2599%25E3%2580%258D%25E5%2587%25BA%25E5%2580%258B%25E6%259C%25AA%25E4%25BE%2586/cmbz/568270120cf236d40391776a%7Ctitle=bizhkmag%7Cwebsite=bizhkmag%7Caccess-date=2016-03-09|title=BizHK創業人誌|website=BizHK創業人誌|access-date=5 August 2016}}</ref>

=== Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) ===
On 4 November 2015, Kelvin has drawn up a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Korean Government as the founder of the only one Hong Kong-based corporate in selling products solely from Korean.

=== Breaking Guinness World Record – The Largest Cardboard Sculpture ===
On 4 April 2016, [[Discovery Park (Hong Kong)|Discovery Park]] ([[Tsuen Wan]]) has used a paper maze castle, designed & tailor-made by Kelvin's company Korean Corner in breaking the Guinness World Record of "The Largest Cardboard Sculpture" with the dimension of 10.156 X 10.136 meters. This event has been widely reported by the local media including [[Apple Daily]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/realtime/news/20160404/54947953|title=【李八方online】全球最大紙板雕塑 原來係個「紙迷宮」|website=Apple Daily |language=zh|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/news/art/20160405/19558140|title=隔牆有耳：逾千家庭畫迷宮慶兒童節|website=Apple Daily |language=zh|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref> SkyPost,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skypost.hk/%25E5%2589%25AF%25E5%2588%258A/%25E5%25A5%25BD%25E5%258E%25BB%25E8%2599%2595/20160329/007/%25E6%2599%25BA%25E8%2583%25BD%25E6%25B4%25BB%25E5%258B%2595%25E4%25B8%2589%25E9%2587%258D%25E5%25A5%258F/211101|title=《晴報》─智能活動三重奏|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref> Parenting Headline,{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}<!-- WP:RS needed; removed link to WP:SPS (Twitter, FB, WP)--><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.parentingheadline.com/index.php/zh/%E8%A6%AA%E5%AD%90%E9%A0%AD%E6%A2%9D/%E6%9C%80%E6%96%B0%E6%B4%BB%E5%8B%95/2860-%E3%80%90%E8%A6%AA%E5%AD%90%E5%A5%BD%E5%8E%BB%E8%99%95%E3%80%91%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E6%9C%80%E5%A4%A7%E7%9A%84%E7%B4%99%E6%9D%BF%E9%9B%95%E5%A1%91|title=【親子好去處】全球最大的紙板雕塑|website=|access-date=}}</ref> Education Post HK<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.educationpost.com.hk/zh-hk/resources/parents-guide/160331-family-time-d-park|title=MI Super Run – ｢多元智能｣兒童全能跑挑戰賽|website=Education Post|access-date=24 June 2016}}</ref> etc.

=== TVB J2 – <<Own Sweet Home - The 287th Episode>><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mytv.tvb.com/tc/cat_lifestyle/ownsweethome/257617|title=myTV – 生活消閒 – 安樂蝸 – 第 287 集|website=mytv.tvb.com|access-date=27 June 2016}}</ref> ===
